1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,090
Here are two specific things to do to build confidence through efficient management of your memory bank.

2
00:00:07,760 --> 00:00:08,370
1.

3
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:12,690
Deposit only positive thoughts in your memory bank.

4
00:00:13,040 --> 00:00:14,769
Let's face it squarely.

5
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:20,690
Everyone encounters plenty of unpleasant, embarrassing, and discouraging situations.

6
00:00:20,880 --> 00:00:27,409
But unsuccessful and successful people deal with these situations in directly opposite ways.

7
00:00:27,760 --> 00:00:31,170
Unsuccessful people take them to heart, so to speak.

8
00:00:31,360 --> 00:00:37,170
They dwell on the unpleasant situations, thereby giving them a good start in their memory.

9
00:00:37,440 --> 00:00:40,129
They don't take their minds away from them.

10
00:00:40,320 --> 00:00:45,009
At night, the unpleasant situation is the last thing they think about.

11
00:00:45,680 --> 00:00:50,690
Confident, successful people, on the other hand, don't give it another thought.

12
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:56,450
Successful people specialize in putting positive thoughts into their memory bank.

13
00:00:56,880 --> 00:01:02,370
What kind of performance would your car deliver if every morning before you left for work,

14
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:07,009
you scooped up a double handful of dirt and put it into your crankcase?

15
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:12,129
That fine engine would soon be a mess, unable to do what you want it to do.

16
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:18,289
Negative unpleasant thoughts deposited in your mind affect your mind the same way.

17
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:23,170
Negative thoughts produce needless wear and tear on your mental motor.

18
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:27,409
They create worry, frustration, and feelings of inferiority.

19
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:31,490
They put you beside the road while others drive ahead.

20
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,009
Do this.

21
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:39,009
In these moments when you're alone with your thoughts, when you're driving your car or eating alone,

22
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:41,970
recall pleasant, positive experiences.

23
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:44,690
Put good thoughts in your memory bank.

24
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:46,610
This boosts confidence.

25
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:50,050
It gives you that, I sure feel good feeling.

26
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:53,009
It helps keep your body functioning right too.

27
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:55,649
Here is an excellent plan.

28
00:01:55,840 --> 00:02:00,769
Just before you go to sleep, deposit good thoughts in your memory bank.

29
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:02,450
Count your blessings.

30
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:06,050
Recall the many good things you have to be thankful for.

31
00:02:06,240 --> 00:02:10,210
Your wife or husband, your children, your friends, your health.

32
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:13,730
Recall the good things you saw people do today.

33
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:16,930
Recall your little victories and accomplishments.

34
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:20,850
Go over the reasons why you are glad to be alive.

